    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\n![CleanShot 2024-06-10 at 05 34 49@2x](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/51586292/e0c95a03-7fc8-432e-b50f-5ca96e27648a)\r\nthis is an image of it occurring and creating artifacts. I managed to reproduce it on version 0.10.0 with only these two options\r\n```\r\nvim.opt.cursorline=true\r\nvim.opt.signcolumn=\"yes\"\r\n```\r\nit is a problem when sshing into remote (supercomputer). I think I sometimes get it locally but I can not reproduce it so it may not be true.\r\nwhen it occurs with vsplit, things from the right hand side fall over to the left.\r\n\r\n![CleanShot 2024-06-10 at 19 54 16](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/51586292/f62fbeab-ae9f-47c3-89f3-c5e6ee47a64b)\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nssh into TSUBAME4 https://www.t4.gsic.titech.ac.jp/docs/handbook.en/\r\ngo into an interactive session\r\nqrsh -l cpu_4 -l h_rt=0:10:00\r\n\r\nnvim --clean -u minimal.lua\r\n\r\nminimal.lua:\r\n```\r\nvim.opt.cursorline=true\r\nvim.opt.signcolumn=\"yes\"\r\n```\r\n\r\ncheck by going from unindented line to indented line\r\nexample file:\r\n```\r\n\r\n\t\texample\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nline does not indent backwards\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1713484068\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nssh into remote so idk uname -ra gives Linux r2n6 5.14.0-362.18.1.el9_3.x86_64 #1 SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Wed Jan 3 15:54:45 EST 2024 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nalacritty 0.13.2 (1)\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nappimage",
